TEXAS & P. RY. CO. v. MORRIS et al. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. November 16, 3909.) No. 1,917. In Error to the Circuit Court of the United States for the Eastern District of Texas. F. H. Prendergast, for plaintiff in error. S. P. Jones, for defendants in error.

Before PABDEE, Mc0OBMICK, and SHELBY, Circuit Judges.

PEB CURIAM.

All the assignments of error-in this case complain of erroneous charges to the jury; but the record shows no seasonable exceptions were taken in the court below, either to the judge’s charge as a whole or to any part thereof. The judgment of the Circuit Court is affirmed.
